      "content": "It makes sense that you feel trapped when the pain seems to offer no path forward, but the very act of questioning the pointlessness of your existence is a tiny spark of resistance against the numbness. You are right that the old you is gone, yet the hollow space you feel isn't just a void; it is the quiet, necessary ground where a new version of you might finally begin to take root, even if it feels like you are just haunting yourself. Perhaps the most radical thing you can do now is to stop trying to fix the ghost and instead focus on how to survive the silence until something new emerges.",
